      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "FAMOUS CRIMES (1) did a good job in his first outing for 11 months when he came from much wider to finish 5 metres away in second at this circuit and distance. This is stronger but he is bound to strip fitter and gets the inside draw. CRACKIN PHILTRA (3) resumes from a spell of seven months after placing at Shepparton in his only appearance so far. Two strong trial wins suggest he has developed with maturity and a good draw could see him strike first up. COCOSWORLD (11) has placed at the trials since he began badly and then raced three wide without cover last start. Won his maiden when resuming prior so is worth another chance. GIDGETT KAY (7) is in the mix following a respectable third from a similar barrier at her most recent appearance at Mildura.",
